<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<!--
  Entitlements for the UNSANDBOXED menu-bar host app.

  Daybrief ships as a Developer-ID, unsandboxed menu-bar app (it needs a loopback
  HTTP listener for the Google OAuth PKCE flow, which the App Sandbox network-server
  entitlement does not cover for arbitrary 127.0.0.1 ports, plus unrestricted
  Keychain + Application Support access). The App Sandbox key is therefore
  intentionally absent (defaults to off).

  The one capability added is the App Group: the host writes a small, display-safe
  brief snapshot into the shared group container so the SANDBOXED widget extension
  (which can read nothing else) can render today's brief. The group id is team-
  prefixed at build time via $(DAYBRIEF_APP_GROUP) → $(TeamIdentifierPrefix)…, so no
  literal team ID is committed. See docs/build/widget.md.
-->
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.security.application-groups</key>
	<array>
		<string>$(DAYBRIEF_APP_GROUP)</string>
	</array>
</dict>
</plist>
